          <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a></div>                              <h2>Jack Chiltern&#039;s Wife</h2>                                                  <div class="clear-block">
            <div id="node-148" class="node">



  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <p><a href="http://www.amazon.co.uk/Jack-Chilterns-Mills-Historical-ebook/dp/B00BQGH28A/ref=sr_1_1?s=digital-text&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1368956389&amp;sr=1-1&amp;keywords=Jack+Chiltern%27s+Wife"><img class="productImage" alt="Product Details" src="http://ecx.images-amazon.com/images/I/518nZm8jFwL._AA160_.jpg" /></a>A Wife in Name only</p>
<p>Published&nbsp;as an ebook May 2013</p>
<p>Escaping a marriage she doesn&rsquo;t want, Kitty Harston runs away to fine her brother in France, regardless of he unrest there. She has met Jack, Viscount Chiltern before and when she sees him on the packet crossing the Channel, she is sure he has come after her to return her to England. It may be a coincidence but he cannot leave her to fend for herself, so they pretend to be a married couple, though he realises, even if she does not, that travelling together means they must marry for real to avoid the scandal.<br />
&nbsp;</p>  </div>

